SIMPLE: relent
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Relent
<hw>Re*lent"</hw> <pr>(r?-l?nt")</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Relented</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Relenting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>ralentir</ets>, fr. L. pref. <ets>re-</ets> re- + <ets>ad</ets> to
+ <ets>lentus</ets> pliant, flexible, slow. See <er>Lithe</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To become less rigid or hard; to yield; to dissolve; to
melt; to deliquesce.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He stirred the coals till <qex>relente</qex> gan⟦br⟧
The wax again the fire.</q> <rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[Salt of tartar] placed in a cellar will . . . begin to
<qex>relent</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Boyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When opening buds salute the welcome day,⟦br⟧
And earth, <qex>relenting</qex>, feels the genial ray.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To become less severe or intense; to become less
hard, harsh, cruel, or the like; to soften in temper; to become more
mild and tender; to feel compassion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Can you . . . behold⟦br⟧
My sighs and tears, and will not once <qex>relent</qex>?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Relent</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Relent
<hw>Re*lent"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To slacken; to
abate.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And oftentimes he would <qex>relent</qex> his pace.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To soften; to dissolve.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To mollify ; to cause to be less harsh or
severe.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1214 --></p>

<p><ent>Relent</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Relent
<hw>Re*lent"</hw> <pr>(r?-l?nt")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Stay; stop;
delay.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nor rested till she came without <qex>relent</qex>⟦br⟧
Unto the land of Amazons.</q> <rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Relentless</ent>⟦br⟧
